{"word":"μαρτυρία","slug":"μαρτυρία","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>μαρτυρία, ας, ἡ</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:μαρτυρέω\">μαρτυρέω</a></el>] ‘attestation of a fact or truth’, <b>testimony, witness<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> focus on legal aspect <b><a href='B:480 14:55'>Mk 14:55f</a>, 59; <a href='B:490 22:71'>Lk 22:71</a>; <a href='B:500 8:17'>J 8:17</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> generally in sense of attestation as appraisal or approval <b>1:7, 19</b> and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ oft.\">oft.</a> in J; <b><a href='B:510 22:18'>Ac 22:18</a>; <a href='B:610 3:7'>1 Ti 3:7</a>; <a href='B:630 1:13'>Tit 1:13</a>; <a href='B:690 5:9-11'>1 J 5:9-11</a>; <a href='B:710 1:1'>3 J 12</a>; <a href='B:730 1:2'>Rv 1:2</a></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ al.\">al.</a> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:μαρτυρέω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:μαρτύριον\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}